WEBVTT

00:03.873 --> 00:07.137
The opera is tomorrow night,
and you are not finished.

00:07.268 --> 00:09.748
On the contrary,
I am entirely finished.

00:09.879 --> 00:11.315
[Jacqueline]
This is my torture, Odette.

00:11.446 --> 00:13.274
I have a story for you,
Chevalier.

00:13.404 --> 00:15.711
I took her while
the servant girl was sleeping.

00:15.841 --> 00:16.799
[Pascal] I'm taking you back
to your mother.

00:16.929 --> 00:18.714
[Camille] Valmont!

00:18.844 --> 00:21.064
When one needs him most,
he cannot be relied upon.

00:21.195 --> 00:23.153
-[door bangs open]
-[grunting]

00:23.284 --> 00:24.894
[Gabriel]
A surgeon I've talked with

00:25.025 --> 00:26.722
has found this thread
in another woman.

00:26.852 --> 00:28.419
Are you familiar with
the myth of the Labyrinth?

00:28.550 --> 00:30.987
I will exploit infidelity
where I find it.

00:31.118 --> 00:33.598
[Ondine] If she is trying
to destroy you,

00:33.729 --> 00:35.296
she'll find out she doesn't
know the meaning of the word!

00:35.426 --> 00:37.428
Valmont.

00:37.559 --> 00:39.430
[Camille] I want all of Paris
to know who I am:

00:39.517 --> 00:41.954
one of the most powerful
women in the city.

00:42.085 --> 00:43.869
[Jean] I'll do nothing more.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.262
[Abbayé] You'll do
whatever's asked of you.

00:45.393 --> 00:46.698
Find a girl
who leaves no trace.

00:46.829 --> 00:49.092
[Victoire]
Stay aw--stay away from me!

00:49.223 --> 00:51.834
[tense music plays]

00:52.008 --> 00:54.793
♪ ♪

01:04.064 --> 01:05.456
[Camille groans]

01:19.470 --> 01:22.212
[bell dings]

01:23.779 --> 01:26.564
[bell dings]

01:27.870 --> 01:30.612
[dramatic music plays]

01:30.786 --> 01:33.571
♪ ♪

01:36.705 --> 01:39.490
Majordome, what is this?

01:39.577 --> 01:41.579
Where are the servants?

01:41.710 --> 01:43.581
You do not know your husband's
instructions, Marquise?

01:43.712 --> 01:44.974
The servants are gone.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.671
You're leaving
for Saint-Domingue.

01:46.802 --> 01:48.369
The Marquis intends
for you to reside

01:48.499 --> 01:49.935
there together indefinitely.

01:50.022 --> 01:51.241
I can't leave Paris.

01:52.634 --> 01:53.722
I must be at the opera tonight.

01:53.852 --> 01:55.115
I can't leave!

01:55.245 --> 01:55.985
It is your husband's wish.

01:56.072 --> 01:57.900
It is not mine.

01:58.030 --> 02:01.251
If they are not
the same as his,

02:01.338 --> 02:05.212
your wishes mean nothing...
Marquise.

02:10.782 --> 02:14.134
I wish you... good luck.

02:17.137 --> 02:19.965
♪ ♪

02:41.987 --> 02:44.686
[dramatic string music plays]

02:44.860 --> 02:47.645
♪ ♪

03:46.835 --> 03:48.097
You cannot hold me here.

03:50.186 --> 03:51.840
We can do what we like,
monsieur.

03:51.970 --> 03:54.625
[Pascal grunting]

03:56.453 --> 03:59.239
[child babbling]

04:02.154 --> 04:03.504
[Azolan grunts]

04:03.634 --> 04:04.592
Sir?

04:06.855 --> 04:08.073
[door slams]

04:15.255 --> 04:16.734
[Azolan gasps]

04:16.821 --> 04:19.781
[suspenseful music plays]

04:19.955 --> 04:22.740
♪ ♪

04:24.438 --> 04:25.917
Well, well.

04:27.745 --> 04:29.269
The familiar.

04:39.540 --> 04:42.107
But where is the ungodly
creature you serve?

04:42.238 --> 04:44.284
I don't know, Vicomtesse.

04:44.414 --> 04:45.850
He's out.

04:45.981 --> 04:47.809
I want you
to give him a message.

04:51.203 --> 04:54.642
Tell him his allegiance
with Camille...

04:54.772 --> 04:57.253
will be his downfall.

04:57.384 --> 05:00.604
That is, if it's possible
to fall further.

05:04.347 --> 05:06.044
And tell him to call on me.

05:13.138 --> 05:15.532
I have a proposition for him.

05:15.706 --> 05:18.492
♪ ♪

05:23.018 --> 05:24.411
[Jacqueline] Where is Odette?

05:24.541 --> 05:26.630
-Where is she?
-[Henri] Safe.

05:27.631 --> 05:29.764
To be raised by women
beyond moral failing.

05:29.894 --> 05:31.940
[Jacqueline inhales sharply]

05:32.070 --> 05:35.291
[Henri] I warned you,
Jacqueline, after the ball.

05:35.422 --> 05:38.033
Yet days later,
you try to steal away

05:38.163 --> 05:40.383
with this man and my child!

05:41.341 --> 05:43.734
What do you imagine
a scandal of that magnitude

05:43.821 --> 05:45.432
could do to my career,
to my life?

05:45.562 --> 05:46.911
Your life?

05:50.262 --> 05:51.307
What are you going
to do to Lucienne?

05:53.004 --> 05:55.224
I will make him disappear.

05:55.311 --> 05:57.487
And if there's one word
of this...

05:57.574 --> 05:58.836
[Jacqueline inhales sharply]

05:58.967 --> 06:00.838
...one hint of gossip...

06:03.928 --> 06:07.410
...I'll declare you unsound,
and you'll go to the asylum.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.586
You'll be as good as dead
to any man or child

06:09.717 --> 06:11.501
you may have had affection for.

06:11.632 --> 06:14.417
[dramatic music plays]

06:14.591 --> 06:17.333
♪ ♪

06:22.556 --> 06:23.731
[Edouard] You've done
all that's been asked

06:23.861 --> 06:25.123
of you, Marquis?

06:25.254 --> 06:26.124
I have.

06:29.171 --> 06:31.565
Tell the Duc an Ariadne
awaits him in the usual place.

06:31.695 --> 06:34.437
Oh, he'll be happy
to receive this news.

06:34.568 --> 06:38.310
We feared your enthusiasm
for this work had diminished.

06:38.441 --> 06:39.529
It's at an end now, Edouard.

06:42.358 --> 06:43.881
[Edouard]
Then we'll say adieu...

06:45.796 --> 06:47.885
....until we require
your services again...

06:51.019 --> 06:53.151
...Marquis.

06:53.238 --> 06:56.067
♪ ♪

07:06.687 --> 07:09.516
[grunting]

07:21.745 --> 07:24.531
♪ ♪

07:28.056 --> 07:29.187
Victoire!

07:34.192 --> 07:35.324
Victoire!

07:42.940 --> 07:44.115
Victoire!

07:47.597 --> 07:48.729
Victoire.

08:05.528 --> 08:07.225
Victoire, for God's sakes.

08:23.677 --> 08:26.549
-[cries]
-[tapestry fluttering]

08:30.510 --> 08:33.861
[wind whistling]

09:12.290 --> 09:15.032
[suspenseful music plays]

09:15.206 --> 09:17.948
♪ ♪

10:07.041 --> 10:09.783
[eerie music plays]

10:09.957 --> 10:12.742
♪ ♪

10:50.911 --> 10:52.477
[exhales heavily]

10:55.132 --> 10:57.613
-[Jean] What are you doing?
-[Camille] What is this place?

10:57.744 --> 10:59.006
[Jean] It's an old tunnel
that's no longer used.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.790
Someone's been here.

11:00.921 --> 11:02.574
Victoire!

11:02.705 --> 11:05.142
-[Jean] We need to leave.
-[Victoire] No!

11:05.273 --> 11:06.622
-[Camille] Victoire!
-[Jean] Come back here!

11:06.753 --> 11:08.363
[Camille] Victoire!
[breathing heavily]

11:08.450 --> 11:09.930
Victoire!

11:10.060 --> 11:13.237
Oh, no. Help me.

11:13.324 --> 11:14.717
[Jean] Leave her.

11:14.848 --> 11:15.457
[Camille]
What have you done to her?

11:15.587 --> 11:17.154
[Victoire gasping]

11:17.241 --> 11:18.895
[Jean] She's an Ariadne now.

11:19.026 --> 11:20.157
[Camille] No, Jean!

11:22.377 --> 11:24.074
[Jean] Forget about her.

11:24.945 --> 11:27.077
I'll get you a new girl,
a better girl.

11:27.208 --> 11:29.732
This one is nothing!

11:29.819 --> 11:31.691
This is what my wife
saw in you.

11:35.607 --> 11:36.696
[Camille] She is everything.

11:36.826 --> 11:39.089
[both grunting]

11:41.352 --> 11:42.832
[Jean] How dare you judge me?

11:42.919 --> 11:44.921
You lied your way
into my house.

11:45.052 --> 11:47.358
You lying, blackmailing,
destructive wretch!

11:47.489 --> 11:49.578
[grunts]

11:49.709 --> 11:53.713
[Camille gasping]

11:53.800 --> 11:56.237
[Majordome]
Victoire, are you all right?

11:56.367 --> 11:57.804
[Camille gasping]

11:57.891 --> 12:00.023
[Jean groans]

12:00.154 --> 12:02.939
[tense music plays]

12:03.113 --> 12:05.594
♪ ♪

12:06.377 --> 12:09.250
[Jean choking]

12:16.213 --> 12:19.086
[screams]

12:35.580 --> 12:38.366
♪ ♪

12:45.373 --> 12:47.810
-[Camille moans]
-[Victoire breathing heavily]

12:53.033 --> 12:57.124
[Camille groaning]

12:57.254 --> 12:58.081
[Majordome] He's dead.

12:59.822 --> 13:00.649
He's dead.

13:02.390 --> 13:04.827
[Camille]
This is what she saw in me.

13:04.958 --> 13:07.743
[dramatic music plays]

13:07.917 --> 13:10.659
♪ ♪

13:13.923 --> 13:16.665
[Camille crying]

13:23.803 --> 13:24.760
[manservant] Uh, you cannot
be here, my lady.

13:24.847 --> 13:25.805
[Jacqueline] Be silent.

13:32.724 --> 13:34.465
[Pascal grunts]

13:38.948 --> 13:40.907
[Jacqueline] My husband
intends to punish you.

13:40.994 --> 13:43.431
I could not save you,
even if I wanted to,

13:43.561 --> 13:45.302
but I can help you
save your soul.

13:45.433 --> 13:46.956
Kneel, Monsieur Lucienne.

13:47.087 --> 13:48.871
Ask God for forgiveness.

13:53.006 --> 13:54.094
[Pascal grunts]

13:56.836 --> 13:58.011
My husband has sent Odette away

13:58.141 --> 14:00.622
and threatens me
with the asylum.

14:00.752 --> 14:02.667
Monsieur Lucienne's confession
will be heard in private.

14:02.798 --> 14:03.668
Leave us.

14:03.799 --> 14:04.844
Yes, madame.

14:06.367 --> 14:07.150
[door clatters shut]

14:07.281 --> 14:08.891
I could save you.

14:09.022 --> 14:11.111
How? He intends for you to die.

14:11.198 --> 14:14.244
Do you attend
the queen's opera tonight?

14:14.375 --> 14:16.420
Yes.

14:16.551 --> 14:18.814
Put down in writing all that
you told me, all that you did.

14:18.945 --> 14:19.859
I'll find a way
to meet you there,

14:19.946 --> 14:22.470
before the final act.

14:22.600 --> 14:23.950
I'll make it clear to him
what I will do

14:24.080 --> 14:25.690
if he does not let us go
in peace.

14:27.562 --> 14:30.043
I'll read that letter
to the entire audience.

14:30.173 --> 14:31.174
You would destroy me then.

14:31.305 --> 14:32.306
No.

14:34.438 --> 14:35.875
It will not get that far.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.575
He will choose to save himself.

14:43.230 --> 14:44.840
Jacqueline...

14:44.971 --> 14:48.017
[soft music plays]

14:48.104 --> 14:50.063
...God will always save us.

14:50.237 --> 14:53.022
♪ ♪

14:56.896 --> 14:58.288
May the Lord forgive you.

15:05.295 --> 15:06.731
[Majordome]
I should send for the gardes.

15:10.300 --> 15:12.302
Should you?

15:13.390 --> 15:15.827
If you must seek justice
for a man like that, then do.

15:18.308 --> 15:20.789
[Majordome] He took my name.

15:20.920 --> 15:24.532
20 years ago, when I was
first brought to this house,

15:24.662 --> 15:27.665
I was known only
as the Majordome.

15:32.496 --> 15:34.629
My name is Etienne Joubert.

15:38.241 --> 15:40.069
There will be no gardes.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.766
Leave this to me.

15:43.246 --> 15:44.378
Thank you.

15:46.162 --> 15:47.468
Thank you, Etienne.

15:50.253 --> 15:53.082
[Jacqueline] " I write
this letter to you, my husband,

15:53.213 --> 15:55.563
because I can no longer carry
the burden in my soul

15:55.693 --> 15:57.565
of what you did
all those years ago."

16:17.977 --> 16:20.805
[Camille] Did he--did he do
anything to you?

16:22.807 --> 16:24.200
[Victoire] He didn't touch me.

16:24.853 --> 16:28.378
I'm so sorry... for everything.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.514
For putting you at risk here.

16:37.039 --> 16:38.519
For the things I said.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.262
You're my friend.

16:44.394 --> 16:47.528
You're my best friend.

16:47.615 --> 16:48.964
And you're mine too.

16:50.705 --> 16:52.185
We can have that life now.

16:54.709 --> 16:55.840
He's gone.

17:00.671 --> 17:02.804
It will be you and me...

17:02.891 --> 17:05.067
-Camille.
-...together again.

17:05.198 --> 17:06.460
-We can have that house...
-Camille.

17:06.590 --> 17:07.591
...that little house
you dreamed of.

17:07.722 --> 17:09.767
Camille...

17:09.898 --> 17:11.247
it's time for me to go.

17:15.382 --> 17:16.774
Things will be different
after tonight.

17:16.905 --> 17:18.472
No.

17:18.602 --> 17:19.603
No, Camille.

17:26.958 --> 17:29.048
-Forgive me, Victoire.
-I do.

17:30.266 --> 17:31.398
I do.

17:33.443 --> 17:36.142
But I've decided
I need to go to the New World.

17:36.272 --> 17:39.275
I need to find out who I am.
who I can be without you.

17:39.406 --> 17:41.451
Do you understand that?

17:46.239 --> 17:48.937
I don't know
I can be without you.

17:49.111 --> 17:51.809
♪ ♪

17:59.513 --> 18:01.036
Find peace, Camille.

18:01.167 --> 18:04.213
Please. For me.

18:04.344 --> 18:05.171
[softly] Yeah.

18:06.737 --> 18:09.262
After tonight.

18:16.312 --> 18:18.097
Then let me help you
dress for your battle.

18:18.271 --> 18:21.056
♪ ♪

18:27.149 --> 18:28.498
I cannot accept this.

18:28.629 --> 18:29.934
I believe you just have.

18:30.065 --> 18:32.023
But I have done nothing
to earn it.

18:32.154 --> 18:33.938
I haven't brought
a killer to justice,

18:34.025 --> 18:35.897
and I found
the Labyrinth club closed.

18:36.027 --> 18:38.465
We don't win all the battles,
but we continue with the war.

18:39.683 --> 18:41.120
Which war?

18:41.250 --> 18:45.776
Protecting
our structures of power.

18:45.863 --> 18:47.865
Forget this matter of the club.

18:47.952 --> 18:51.434
Focus on making good men safe.

18:54.829 --> 18:57.571
-[grunting]
-[metallic squeaking]

19:02.532 --> 19:05.274
[soft dramatic music plays]

19:05.448 --> 19:07.058
♪ ♪

19:07.146 --> 19:09.974
[Camille]
I worry how you'll manage.

19:10.061 --> 19:12.368
[Victoire]
As I did before you.

19:12.499 --> 19:13.587
[Camille]
You were in a crab pot.

19:15.937 --> 19:17.460
It was a lobster pot,
and I was--

19:17.591 --> 19:19.332
Mending it.

19:19.462 --> 19:20.637
I know.

19:26.426 --> 19:28.471
Promise me we'll be
together again.

19:31.082 --> 19:32.780
When we're different people.

19:32.910 --> 19:34.912
Better people.

19:43.834 --> 19:46.750
I'm not saying goodbye.

19:46.881 --> 19:48.187
I can't.

19:53.931 --> 19:56.847
Maybe if I don't say it,

19:56.934 --> 19:58.719
you won't really be gone.

20:02.984 --> 20:04.507
Perhaps you'll
change your mind.

20:12.733 --> 20:15.475
♪ ♪

20:20.654 --> 20:23.526
[crying]

20:29.053 --> 20:31.012
[Majordome] For your journey.

20:31.142 --> 20:33.449
She will tell you that she
doesn't need taking care of,

20:33.580 --> 20:34.972
but it's not true;
she'll need you.

20:36.713 --> 20:38.324
She may not always
thank you for that care.

20:38.454 --> 20:39.238
[Majordome chuckles]

20:42.676 --> 20:45.548
I hope to see who you become
in the future.

20:45.679 --> 20:46.854
[Victoire chuckles]

20:46.984 --> 20:48.029
I'm Victoire.

20:48.159 --> 20:49.335
[Majordome chuckles]

20:59.997 --> 21:01.129
You're victorious.

21:01.303 --> 21:03.610
♪ ♪

21:07.744 --> 21:10.530
[dramatic music plays]

21:10.660 --> 21:13.446
♪ ♪'

21:25.458 --> 21:26.807
Where's my husband?

21:27.547 --> 21:29.026
I'm to accompany you
to the opera.

21:30.767 --> 21:32.203
I'm instructed
we should not delay.

21:42.431 --> 21:45.347
[grunting]

21:45.521 --> 21:48.263
♪ ♪

22:12.635 --> 22:14.071
Stop!

22:14.202 --> 22:15.072
-Stop.
-[horse whinnies]

22:15.203 --> 22:16.509
[driver] Whoa there.

22:19.163 --> 22:20.774
We're to go straight
to the opera.

22:20.861 --> 22:22.079
You may serve my husband,
but you're my maid.

22:22.210 --> 22:23.994
This poor boy
depends upon my charity.

22:27.911 --> 22:29.565
Azolan, dear child. Thank God.

22:29.696 --> 22:31.306
-Madame, where's my master?
-He's in my house.

22:31.437 --> 22:32.873
Don't worry.
He'll be with you soon.

22:33.003 --> 22:34.222
Wait for him,
and give him this.

22:43.057 --> 22:44.928
-[whip cracks]
-[horse whinnies]

22:49.890 --> 22:52.675
♪ ♪

22:58.768 --> 22:59.987
[Camille] I have to leave now.

23:01.423 --> 23:02.946
He cannot be found here.

23:05.862 --> 23:09.388
Etienne... please help me.

23:14.871 --> 23:15.916
[Majordome]
No one will find him.

23:17.657 --> 23:20.137
I'll take him by cart
far from Paris.

23:20.268 --> 23:21.574
Let him rot in a ditch.

23:23.619 --> 23:25.099
But if my husband is dead...

23:27.275 --> 23:29.364
...then I am his widow.

23:29.495 --> 23:30.931
And as his widow...

23:33.281 --> 23:35.239
....I still have

23:35.370 --> 23:38.417
the status
that came with my marriage

23:38.547 --> 23:42.159
and the power
of my dead husband.

23:42.290 --> 23:43.944
His body must be found.

23:44.074 --> 23:46.903
[dark music plays]

23:47.077 --> 23:49.819
♪ ♪

23:52.387 --> 23:55.129
[indistinct chatter]

23:57.697 --> 23:59.350
[horse whinnies]

24:02.397 --> 24:04.965
[indistinct chatter]

24:14.583 --> 24:16.063
Oh, look.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.761
What?

24:18.892 --> 24:23.984
The most meteoric rise
since Christ on the third day.

24:24.114 --> 24:26.552
-Did you hear?
-What?

24:26.639 --> 24:28.075
She's married
the bloody Marquis.

24:28.205 --> 24:29.772
[Eloise gasps]

24:35.735 --> 24:37.214
[baton tapping]

24:39.390 --> 24:41.871
[horn fanfare playing]

24:42.045 --> 24:44.787
♪ ♪

25:07.984 --> 25:10.726
[applause]

25:17.167 --> 25:21.345
Majesty, ladies and gentlemen,

25:21.476 --> 25:24.261
I give you something
we see little of:

25:24.392 --> 25:26.394
truth.

25:26.525 --> 25:29.266
Everything you see tonight
has happened,

25:29.353 --> 25:31.355
and everyone within it

25:31.442 --> 25:33.793
is in this theater.

25:33.923 --> 25:35.490
[audience gasps]

25:35.621 --> 25:39.146
I give you...
The Opera of Paris.

25:39.276 --> 25:41.278
[applause]

25:44.717 --> 25:47.284
[grand orchestral music
playing]

25:47.458 --> 25:50.287
♪ ♪

25:52.899 --> 25:56.729
♪ There is a power ♪

25:56.903 --> 26:00.950
♪ In secrets of others ♪

26:01.124 --> 26:03.083
♪ Find them, guard them ♪

26:03.257 --> 26:04.911
♪ Use them ♪

26:05.085 --> 26:07.957
♪ For secrets are the power
Of our sex ♪

26:08.131 --> 26:09.176
♪ ♪

26:09.306 --> 26:12.179
[vocalizing]

26:12.353 --> 26:15.138
♪ ♪

26:21.754 --> 26:23.843
♪ The secrets are the power ♪

26:24.017 --> 26:28.325
♪ Of our sex ♪

26:28.499 --> 26:31.285
♪ ♪

26:34.375 --> 26:36.333
[applause]

26:40.729 --> 26:42.862
[singer as Camille]
♪ I am the girl ♪

26:43.036 --> 26:47.518
♪ You do not see... ♪

26:49.129 --> 26:50.652
-[Azolan] Sir!
-[Pascal] Azolan.

26:50.783 --> 26:52.567
[Azolan]
What have they done to you?

26:52.698 --> 26:54.308
-We must hurry.
-Let's get to the opera.

26:54.438 --> 26:56.092
You must help Camille.

26:56.179 --> 26:57.311
[singer as Camille]
♪ Lonely place ♪

26:57.485 --> 26:58.834
♪ ♪

26:59.008 --> 27:04.231
♪ I long for ♪

27:04.405 --> 27:10.106
♪ A mother ♪

27:10.280 --> 27:13.066
♪ ♪

27:15.590 --> 27:17.592
[applause]

27:20.508 --> 27:25.078
♪ I will be a mother ♪

27:25.252 --> 27:26.514
♪ ♪

27:26.688 --> 27:32.172
♪ And you will be a daughter ♪

27:32.346 --> 27:34.000
♪ ♪

27:34.174 --> 27:38.700
[singer as Camille]
♪ I will be a daughter ♪

27:38.874 --> 27:40.180
♪ ♪

27:40.354 --> 27:45.533
♪ And you will be a mother ♪

27:45.707 --> 27:47.100
♪ ♪

27:47.187 --> 27:50.016
[both vocalizing]

27:50.190 --> 27:53.367
♪ ♪

27:53.715 --> 27:56.544
♪ We have found ♪

27:56.631 --> 28:00.722
♪ Precious sanctuary ♪

28:00.896 --> 28:03.507
♪ We have found ♪

28:03.682 --> 28:09.296
♪ Precious sanctuary ♪

28:09.470 --> 28:10.950
♪ ♪

28:11.080 --> 28:13.039
[Jacqueline]
I am Madame Montrachet,

28:13.169 --> 28:15.694
but I'll be a mother to you.

28:15.824 --> 28:19.262
[applause]

28:19.349 --> 28:22.048
[bright orchestral music
playing]

28:22.222 --> 28:24.964
♪ ♪

28:59.041 --> 29:01.870
[music intensifies]

29:02.044 --> 29:04.743
♪ ♪

29:07.006 --> 29:08.790
-[fabric tears]
-[audience gasps]

29:08.921 --> 29:10.096
[Jacqueline]
She says she's with child.

29:10.226 --> 29:11.532
Jacqueline, my love.

29:11.662 --> 29:12.185
That you took her
against her will.

29:12.272 --> 29:13.360
She is lying!

29:13.490 --> 29:15.014
She wants all that you have,

29:15.144 --> 29:16.972
all that you would lose
if you believed her.

29:17.146 --> 29:18.191
[singer as Henri]
♪ This must be ♪

29:18.365 --> 29:23.718
♪ Our secret ♪

29:23.892 --> 29:27.113
♪ ♪

29:27.809 --> 29:30.159
Now you know
why I've acted as I did.

29:30.246 --> 29:31.770
You'd do anything
to avenge Camille.

29:33.467 --> 29:36.165
I am now in this
impossible situation.

29:40.256 --> 29:42.563
If I do not give her
the letter,

29:42.693 --> 29:44.260
she will think
that I have failed her.

29:47.873 --> 29:50.789
If I do, she will learn that
her daughter did not die...

29:50.963 --> 29:56.620
♪ He asked me to dance ♪

29:56.707 --> 29:58.100
...but is lost to her.

29:58.187 --> 30:03.323
♪ I knew not what he meant ♪

30:04.280 --> 30:06.456
By destroying them,
I will destroy Camille.

30:06.630 --> 30:10.025
[singer as Camille]
♪ I was an ♪

30:10.199 --> 30:15.857
♪ Innocent ♪

30:16.031 --> 30:20.775
♪ ♪

30:20.906 --> 30:23.386
[dramatic orchestral music
plays]

30:23.560 --> 30:26.694
♪ ♪

30:26.825 --> 30:29.392
[horse whinnies,
hooves clopping]

30:29.566 --> 30:32.091
♪ ♪

30:44.625 --> 30:46.845
[singer as Jacqueline]
♪ You have brought such shame ♪

30:47.019 --> 30:49.891
♪ ♪

30:50.065 --> 30:52.241
[singer as Camille]
♪ Forgive me, forgive me ♪

30:52.415 --> 30:55.244
♪ I am not to blame ♪

30:55.418 --> 30:58.900
[singer as Jacqueline]
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

30:59.074 --> 31:01.250
[singer as Camille]
♪ Please do not send me out ♪

31:01.381 --> 31:04.471
Even God does not forgive.

31:04.645 --> 31:07.343
[singer as Camille]
♪ Please do not send me out ♪

31:07.517 --> 31:10.520
[singer as Jacqueline]
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:10.607 --> 31:13.045
♪ Get out, get out, get out ♪

31:13.219 --> 31:15.917
♪ ♪

31:17.832 --> 31:19.573
[audience murmuring]

31:19.747 --> 31:22.576
♪ ♪

31:24.230 --> 31:26.014
[audience gasps]

31:26.188 --> 31:30.236
[singers]
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:30.410 --> 31:31.977
♪ ♪

31:32.151 --> 31:35.763
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:35.937 --> 31:38.070
♪ ♪

31:38.244 --> 31:40.942
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:41.116 --> 31:44.598
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:44.772 --> 31:47.383
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:47.470 --> 31:50.343
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:50.430 --> 31:53.433
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:53.607 --> 31:56.436
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

31:56.610 --> 31:59.918
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

32:00.005 --> 32:02.616
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

32:02.790 --> 32:05.619
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

32:05.793 --> 32:08.665
♪ Even God does not forgive ♪

32:08.752 --> 32:11.755
♪ Even God does not ♪

32:11.930 --> 32:17.022
♪ Forgive ♪

32:17.979 --> 32:20.808
[breathing heavily]

32:34.691 --> 32:37.346
[breathing heavily]

32:39.087 --> 32:40.219
Camille.

32:45.572 --> 32:47.226
Goodness.

32:57.410 --> 33:01.153
You exalt a peasant
and condemn us?

33:01.283 --> 33:03.894
We are the nobility!

33:03.982 --> 33:07.028
We are their betters!

33:07.115 --> 33:08.812
[person] Yes. Hear, hear.

33:08.943 --> 33:10.901
[Duc de Lanvin]
You disrespect us, Chevalier.

33:11.032 --> 33:12.686
Shame!

33:12.773 --> 33:14.775
[audience] Shame! Shame!

33:14.905 --> 33:18.387
Shame! Shame!

33:21.434 --> 33:22.130
[Camille] Madame.

33:27.788 --> 33:29.311
[tense music plays]

33:29.442 --> 33:31.313
Don't run from me,
Jacqueline de Montrachet.

33:36.231 --> 33:38.407
[Jacqueline] All of that--
that opera--was you?

33:40.366 --> 33:41.845
Why, Camille?

33:41.932 --> 33:44.196
You knew what he did to me,

33:44.326 --> 33:46.415
and you stood by him.

33:46.546 --> 33:48.330
You did not let me
bury my child!

33:48.417 --> 33:49.331
I-I couldn't go against him.

33:49.462 --> 33:51.116
You chose not to.

33:51.246 --> 33:53.161
You didn't want to lose
what you had with him:

33:53.292 --> 33:54.684
your status,

33:54.815 --> 33:55.946
your safety.

33:56.077 --> 33:57.165
You imagine I have safety?

33:57.296 --> 33:58.949
You let him hurt me.

34:00.168 --> 34:01.909
You let him ruin me.

34:01.996 --> 34:03.954
I've lived with it
every day since.

34:09.003 --> 34:10.700
The consequences
were too great.

34:13.529 --> 34:15.096
They were too great.

34:17.664 --> 34:20.232
But if I could,

34:20.362 --> 34:22.234
if I could go back
and change it, I...

34:24.453 --> 34:25.802
...I would protect you.

34:31.765 --> 34:32.766
I loved you.

34:47.737 --> 34:50.088
[Camille] Then help me.

34:50.218 --> 34:52.786
Come back to the opera.

34:52.916 --> 34:56.442
Tell those people
what they saw was the truth.

34:58.008 --> 35:00.185
That it is him in the story.

35:00.315 --> 35:02.752
That a man like that
cannot be at the king's side.

35:02.839 --> 35:04.841
Camille, I-I-I must leave.

35:04.928 --> 35:06.669
I must leave
before it's too late for me.

35:07.975 --> 35:09.455
Still you protect him?

35:09.542 --> 35:10.412
[Jacqueline]
I'm not protecting him.

35:10.543 --> 35:13.241
I'm-I'm escaping him.

35:13.328 --> 35:15.591
I'm leaving Paris tonight
with a man

35:15.722 --> 35:18.072
who has heard my confession,
yet still loves me.

35:18.203 --> 35:20.640
You are leaving
because you are in love,

35:20.770 --> 35:22.511
not because of what he did.

35:22.642 --> 35:25.123
I must go, but I pray for you
that you find someone

35:25.253 --> 35:26.863
who will make this all
fade away.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.958
[dramatic music plays]

35:35.133 --> 35:38.266
♪ ♪

35:38.658 --> 35:40.181
Someone like Lucienne?

35:44.490 --> 35:46.666
You know Lucienne?

35:48.668 --> 35:50.278
I created him.

35:54.978 --> 35:58.982
I've paid him, in many ways,

35:59.113 --> 36:00.419
to make you love him.

36:05.946 --> 36:07.643
And... [laughs]

36:07.774 --> 36:09.297
...he did it all
for some new clothes

36:09.384 --> 36:11.343
and a way back into my bed.

36:18.001 --> 36:19.394
You're lying.

36:22.919 --> 36:25.835
When you were covered in blood

36:25.922 --> 36:28.969
at the church
of Saint-Sauveur,

36:29.056 --> 36:30.579
into whose arms did you fall?

36:32.625 --> 36:34.017
[Jacqueline gasps]

36:35.976 --> 36:38.935
Everything he's ever said
to you

36:39.022 --> 36:40.807
was a lie I made him tell...

36:44.202 --> 36:45.507
...to draw a letter from you.

36:46.987 --> 36:49.903
[crying]

36:57.432 --> 36:58.955
Do not put your faith
in Lucienne.

37:07.312 --> 37:08.748
Tell your husband...

37:08.835 --> 37:10.271
[door clatters open]

37:10.402 --> 37:12.752
...the higher he rises,

37:12.882 --> 37:15.755
the higher I will climb

37:15.885 --> 37:17.670
until I bring him down.

37:17.800 --> 37:19.019
[indistinct chatter]

37:19.149 --> 37:22.109
Till I make him pay.

37:22.240 --> 37:24.807
Till he suffers as I suffered.

37:29.595 --> 37:31.031
When does it end, Camille?

37:34.556 --> 37:36.384
When does it end?

37:38.908 --> 37:40.258
It doesn't.

37:47.613 --> 37:50.355
♪ ♪

38:18.339 --> 38:21.168
[indistinct chatter]

38:31.265 --> 38:32.701
-[wolf whistle]
-[person clicking tongue]

38:32.832 --> 38:34.660
[person] Hello.

38:34.790 --> 38:35.487
-[person] Hoo-hoo!
-[person] How much for you?

38:41.057 --> 38:43.886
[laughter]

38:54.157 --> 38:56.812
Have you come
to judge us, madam?

38:57.509 --> 38:59.249
I know what it takes
to survive here.

39:00.990 --> 39:02.818
I come to honor you.

39:02.905 --> 39:05.691
♪ ♪

39:07.127 --> 39:09.738
[indistinct chatter]

39:09.912 --> 39:12.698
♪ ♪

39:40.465 --> 39:42.467
[laughter]

39:50.300 --> 39:51.867
[horse whinnies]

40:01.442 --> 40:04.140
[soft dramatic music plays]

40:04.314 --> 40:07.143
♪ ♪

40:09.015 --> 40:10.016
You're here.

40:11.670 --> 40:12.888
Of course I'm here.

40:15.195 --> 40:16.936
All I've been trying to do
is get back to you.

40:19.939 --> 40:22.637
I love you, Camille.

40:29.078 --> 40:30.210
I love you.

40:31.864 --> 40:33.561
What happened to you?

40:33.648 --> 40:35.302
[Pascal] I need to tell you
about Jacqueline.

40:36.869 --> 40:38.305
I don't want to talk about her.

40:38.392 --> 40:40.263
-Let me explain.
-[Camille] No.

40:40.394 --> 40:42.004
She's gone.

40:48.228 --> 40:49.272
And I'm yours.

40:53.538 --> 40:55.061
Now I want to live again.

40:57.063 --> 40:59.848
♪ ♪

41:01.284 --> 41:02.938
[soft banging]

41:03.069 --> 41:05.506
[hooves clopping]

41:32.446 --> 41:35.057
I warned you,

41:35.188 --> 41:36.668
and you did not heed me.

41:36.798 --> 41:39.888
[tense music plays]

41:40.062 --> 41:42.848
♪ ♪

41:45.111 --> 41:47.722
[bell ringing]

41:54.599 --> 41:56.296
You will be ruined.

41:58.341 --> 42:00.735
Wherever I am, I will feel it!

42:01.606 --> 42:03.782
And if the price
of your destruction is me,

42:03.869 --> 42:05.784
I will pay it!

42:05.914 --> 42:09.744
[screaming]

42:09.918 --> 42:12.660
♪ ♪

42:31.940 --> 42:33.768
Everything's a map.

42:40.340 --> 42:41.863
-Every line.
-Every line.

42:48.827 --> 42:51.177
-Every scar.
-Every line, every scar.

42:51.307 --> 42:52.744
Mm.

42:54.310 --> 42:56.138
The paths we've taken.

42:56.269 --> 42:58.097
[Camille]
The paths we've taken.

42:58.227 --> 42:59.577
-The things we've done.
-The things we've done.

42:59.707 --> 43:01.448
Things...

43:01.535 --> 43:02.362
-[Camille] The things...
-[both] ...we will do.

43:08.760 --> 43:10.370
-[Pascal] We're all maps.
-[Camille] We're all just maps

43:10.500 --> 43:14.374
and somehow, we find our way

43:14.504 --> 43:16.376
to the things we want.

43:16.463 --> 43:19.292
♪ ♪

43:48.669 --> 43:51.454
[Pascal moaning]

44:13.781 --> 44:16.654
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

44:16.741 --> 44:19.482
[dramatic music plays]

44:19.657 --> 44:22.137
♪ ♪

44:22.268 --> 44:24.792
[door clatters open]

44:24.923 --> 44:27.316
You'll have to find
another girl.

44:27.403 --> 44:29.492
I don't work here, monsieur.

44:29.623 --> 44:31.538
[drunk] A girl like you
will be here forever.

44:32.278 --> 44:33.366
[grunts]

44:33.496 --> 44:34.759
[metallic clatter]

44:34.846 --> 44:37.413
[person groaning]

44:42.897 --> 44:44.333
I'm meant for better things.

44:44.507 --> 44:47.293
♪ ♪

45:00.654 --> 45:01.786
[Edouard] The owner
of the Labyrinth club

45:01.916 --> 45:03.483
was found dead
from a carriage accident

45:03.613 --> 45:06.181
in the streets last night.

45:06.312 --> 45:08.531
The Marquis de Merteuil.

45:10.925 --> 45:14.015
So... the matter is closed.

45:14.146 --> 45:16.278
The household
has been informed.

45:16.409 --> 45:18.803
[tense music plays]

45:18.890 --> 45:21.719
♪ ♪

45:39.519 --> 45:42.261
[indistinct chatter]

45:49.355 --> 45:50.312
[door slams]

45:52.271 --> 45:54.708
[Azolan] I saw Camille leave.

45:54.839 --> 45:56.318
She seemed so happy.

45:56.449 --> 45:57.450
[Pascal] I couldn't tell her.

45:59.669 --> 46:00.670
What do we do?

46:01.976 --> 46:03.282
We are going to find Odette.

46:04.892 --> 46:07.286
And when we do,

46:07.416 --> 46:09.549
that is when I will tell her.

46:09.679 --> 46:11.333
Until then,
you and I will have to carry

46:11.464 --> 46:13.248
this secret in our hearts.

46:18.079 --> 46:19.211
I, um--

46:20.995 --> 46:23.345
I forgot to give you this.

46:23.476 --> 46:25.130
Your stepmother came yesterday.

46:25.260 --> 46:27.045
She knows all about
you and Camille.

46:27.132 --> 46:30.526
She wants your help
and has a proposition for you.

46:42.843 --> 46:44.236
The body has been found.

46:44.366 --> 46:45.324
A-a carriage accident
in the road.

46:45.454 --> 46:46.368
You're in mourning.

46:49.197 --> 46:51.025
We were informed last night.

46:51.939 --> 46:52.984
There's an officer here
to see you.

46:56.465 --> 46:58.467
I suggest you've been walking,

46:58.598 --> 47:00.948
so grieved are you
at the loss of your husband.

47:10.566 --> 47:13.178
Forgive me, Marquise...

47:13.308 --> 47:15.049
but this matter cannot wait.

47:15.223 --> 47:18.009
♪ ♪

47:24.145 --> 47:25.668
I'll keep my visit brief.

47:28.410 --> 47:29.803
I believe your husband
was murdered.

47:32.110 --> 47:36.027
My husband was run over
by a carriage.

47:36.157 --> 47:39.291
There's a rope burn to his neck

47:39.421 --> 47:41.293
which could not be the result
of a carriage accident.

47:42.990 --> 47:44.296
When did you first learn

47:44.426 --> 47:45.601
of your husband's death,
Marquise?

47:47.342 --> 47:49.083
Before or after the opera?

47:49.214 --> 47:53.174
I would hardly go to the opera,
learning such news.

47:53.261 --> 47:54.306
And yet you're not dressed
for grief.

47:54.480 --> 47:57.265
♪ ♪

48:13.978 --> 48:15.588
[Camille gasps]

48:15.718 --> 48:16.415
[Gabriel] Rope burns.

48:18.199 --> 48:19.505
Lift your veil.

48:19.635 --> 48:21.507
-I'm mourning.
-I said lift your veil.

48:31.299 --> 48:32.126
Camille?

48:38.263 --> 48:39.917
-My Camille.
-Don't.

48:40.874 --> 48:42.267
I thought you were dead.

48:42.397 --> 48:45.444
I-I buried you,

48:45.531 --> 48:47.402
and all the time,
you've been here.

48:47.533 --> 48:49.100
I will give you money.

48:49.230 --> 48:51.363
I will give you
whatever you want.

48:51.493 --> 48:53.626
-I want you!
-I'm not at Jericho's now.

48:53.713 --> 48:55.541
Because I bought you.

48:55.671 --> 48:57.891
I paid for you.

48:58.022 --> 48:59.545
-[Camille] No.
-You're mine!

48:59.675 --> 49:01.634
I'm not. I cannot be yours.

49:01.764 --> 49:05.072
Because you love him, Valmont?

49:05.203 --> 49:07.814
Let me go.
I will do whatever you want.

49:09.468 --> 49:11.470
But let me go.

49:17.998 --> 49:19.478
I want you to love me.

49:23.569 --> 49:25.179
I cannot love you.

49:26.441 --> 49:28.356
I do not.

49:28.487 --> 49:29.662
I could never love you.

49:29.792 --> 49:31.751
Then you will not love him,

49:31.881 --> 49:33.274
and you will not love
any other man.

49:33.405 --> 49:35.755
[Camille grunting]

49:40.020 --> 49:41.979
And then,

49:42.066 --> 49:43.763
however long it takes...

49:48.420 --> 49:50.291
...when you finally know
what it is to be alone...

49:51.684 --> 49:52.946
...you will love me.

50:01.999 --> 50:05.089
And if you wish to save
Valmont's life,

50:05.176 --> 50:06.481
write to him.

50:08.831 --> 50:12.226
Tell him...

50:12.313 --> 50:13.358
that you will never
see him again.

50:13.488 --> 50:14.228
[Camille] No.

50:17.405 --> 50:18.276
Yes.

50:20.234 --> 50:22.280
Tell him whatever you must
to finish this.

50:22.454 --> 50:25.239
♪ ♪

50:30.244 --> 50:31.419
Do this...

50:34.292 --> 50:36.381
...or you will hang.

50:47.261 --> 50:50.047
[soft dramatic music plays]

50:50.221 --> 50:53.006
♪ ♪

51:03.451 --> 51:05.105
[Camille] My beloved Valmont...

51:08.500 --> 51:10.589
...there is much to confess.

51:12.852 --> 51:15.420
I have committed
a terrible sin against you.

51:18.118 --> 51:20.077
One which you will
never forgive me for.

51:23.167 --> 51:26.083
All that I have accused you
of, I have done myself.

51:28.389 --> 51:29.782
I've played a game with you.

51:31.000 --> 51:32.959
In truth,

51:33.090 --> 51:35.309
I never forgave you,

51:35.440 --> 51:36.963
and I never intended to.

51:38.921 --> 51:42.577
I have used you
every day since

51:42.664 --> 51:45.102
so that I might flourish
in a world

51:45.232 --> 51:47.060
I would otherwise
have been devoured by.

51:48.975 --> 51:52.805
Through you, I laid
a trail for Jacqueline.

51:52.935 --> 51:56.069
Through you,
I came to Saint-Honoré.

51:58.593 --> 52:01.553
Through you,
I found a marquis,

52:01.640 --> 52:05.209
and I used the same
simplistic tools on him.

52:08.168 --> 52:10.170
Men think they pluck us

52:10.301 --> 52:13.478
when we are ripe
and at our sweetest.

52:13.608 --> 52:15.654
Our skill is in letting them
believe that.

52:18.744 --> 52:21.703
Though brief, my marriage
has given me everything

52:21.834 --> 52:23.792
I could have ever wanted...

52:25.403 --> 52:27.056
...wealth,

52:27.187 --> 52:29.146
a title,

52:29.276 --> 52:30.451
and widowhood.

52:33.454 --> 52:36.065
And as a widow,

52:36.196 --> 52:39.068
I cannot compromise myself

52:39.156 --> 52:40.766
by the acquaintance of a man

52:40.896 --> 52:42.550
with a reputation
such as yours.

52:44.987 --> 52:47.816
♪ ♪

52:50.689 --> 52:51.994
[banging on door]

52:58.653 --> 52:59.437
[Pascal] Where is she?

52:59.567 --> 53:01.090
Camille!

53:01.221 --> 53:02.614
I don't believe what you wrote!

53:02.744 --> 53:05.094
I know what you feel for me!

53:06.270 --> 53:08.489
[Camille] So there is
nothing to hope for, Valmont.

53:10.274 --> 53:13.277
Monsieur! I'm to tell you
every word is true,

53:13.407 --> 53:14.974
and you are never
to come here again.

53:20.414 --> 53:22.938
A warning to you,
for your own safety.

53:25.637 --> 53:28.074
[Camille]
Don't come to me again.

53:28.161 --> 53:29.728
I will not see you.

53:34.515 --> 53:36.213
Then damn you, Camille.

53:38.867 --> 53:40.608
Damn all of what we might
have had together.

53:44.308 --> 53:47.049
[Camille]
Let me simply acknowledge

53:47.136 --> 53:49.356
what we both always knew.

53:55.754 --> 53:57.234
[door slams]

53:57.321 --> 53:58.757
I don't know how to love.

54:07.200 --> 54:09.071
It is beyond my control.

54:19.386 --> 54:20.953
And we are even now.

54:24.130 --> 54:26.828
♪ ♪

54:41.669 --> 54:43.715
I understand you have
a proposition for me.

54:45.586 --> 54:47.414
I do,

54:47.545 --> 54:48.763
but it depends...

54:52.767 --> 54:55.640
...upon where
your loyalty lies:

54:55.770 --> 54:59.252
with this family

54:59.383 --> 55:01.472
or the woman
you are in league with.

55:03.735 --> 55:05.040
Those are my terms.

55:09.828 --> 55:11.786
Your terms.

55:11.917 --> 55:14.702
[dramatic music plays]

55:14.833 --> 55:17.052
[Pascal scoffs]

55:17.183 --> 55:20.665
This proposition
depends upon...

55:20.795 --> 55:22.231
my terms.

55:30.414 --> 55:32.416
Sit down, Vicomtesse.

55:37.116 --> 55:39.901
♪ ♪

55:50.695 --> 55:53.262
And listen.

55:53.437 --> 55:56.265
♪ ♪

56:00.269 --> 56:03.055
[bell tolling]

56:11.933 --> 56:14.719
♪ ♪

56:17.286 --> 56:20.202
[priest]
The Marquis de Merteuil:

56:20.333 --> 56:22.683
a noble of the sword,

56:22.814 --> 56:26.252
his family allied to
the royal house for centuries.

56:28.036 --> 56:31.388
With no heir,
he leaves behind his widow.

56:33.215 --> 56:36.393
Let us pray
for the Widow de Merteuil.

56:38.917 --> 56:43.051
New to Paris, before
her marriage to the Marquis,

56:43.182 --> 56:45.489
she brought light
to the darkness

56:45.619 --> 56:48.230
her late husband
was consumed by.

56:50.145 --> 56:52.452
And though she now
finds herself

56:52.583 --> 56:56.238
in that same darkness
of loss,

56:56.369 --> 56:59.285
she should remember
in the time to come

56:59.416 --> 57:02.680
that the Lord does not abandon
the pure of heart

57:02.810 --> 57:05.813
but sends his messenger
to watch over her.

57:08.642 --> 57:13.299
Let us ask the Lord
to bring comfort and guidance

57:13.386 --> 57:15.867
so that even in her grief,

57:15.997 --> 57:18.913
the Widow de Merteuil
may find her way

57:19.000 --> 57:22.047
without the man she has lost.

57:22.177 --> 57:23.352
Amen.

57:23.483 --> 57:25.311
[all] Amen.

57:38.237 --> 57:40.326
[somber music playing,
choir singing in Latin]

57:40.500 --> 57:43.285
♪ ♪

58:06.526 --> 58:08.833
I'm so sorry for your loss.

58:29.810 --> 58:32.030
No more words for me,
Widow de Merteuil?

58:32.204 --> 58:35.033
♪ ♪

58:36.730 --> 58:38.819
[Camille] If you love me,

58:38.950 --> 58:40.299
walk away, Valmont.

58:42.040 --> 58:43.345
Love you?

58:48.176 --> 58:50.439
It's war between us now.

58:50.527 --> 58:53.355
♪ ♪
